es to make marinade. Poach chicken breasts 10 to 15 minutes over low flame. Cool in liquid. Shred. Mix together shredded chicken, onions, and lettuce. Serve over rice noodles that have been cooked in hot oil in wok.'),(38,'Chinese Fried Rice','https://therecipecritic.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/easy_fried_rice-1-500x500.jpg','diced ham, pork or chicken - oil - chopped green onions - sliced mushrooms (optional) - cold cooked rice - soy sauce - egg - tbsp','Saute onion and meat in oil. Add other ingredients except egg. Cook on low heat about 15 to 20 minutes. Beat egg with a tablespoon of milk. Melt butter in skillet, pour in egg and cook until solid. Slice in thin strips to put over the rice as garnish on the platter.'),(39,'Chinese Pepper Steak','https://www.kitchensanctuary.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Black-Pepper-Beef-square-FS-26.jpg','round steak, cut 1 inch thick - cornstarch - ginger - sugar - sauce - peppers - onion - oil - garlic - water - dry sherry - tomatoes, halved','Partially freeze steak and cut into thin strips. Combine cornstarch, sugar, ginger, and soy sauce. Pour over meat and stir. Cut into thin strips. Quickly brown meat in hot oil and remove. Add green pepper, onion, and garlic. Add water. Cook 5 to 6 minutes. Stir in meat, tomatoes and sherry. Serve over rice.'),(40,'Chinese Roast Pork','https://tasteasianfood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/rp12-feature-600x300.jpg','sugar - salt - soy sauce - h1y - chicken bouillon - fresh pork butt or shoulder of pork','Mix sugar, salt, h1y, soy sauce, and bouillon. Cut pork lengthwise and soak in marinade for 45 minutes. Turning. Place on rack in roasting pan. Dd few tablespoons water to prevent smoking. Bake 350 degrees for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Turning occasionally.'),(41,'Chinese Stir Fried Chicken with Peanuts','https://assets.bonappetit.com/photos/5e99ce1f657e4f00088aced7/1:1/w_2560%2Cc_limit/Basically-Chicken-Stir-Fry.jpg','dry sherry - cornstarch - vegetable oil - b1less chicken, cut in cubes - ginger root - green peppers - green onions - crushed red pepper - unsalted peanuts - soy sauce - cornstarch - water','Mix sherry and cornstarch. Stir chicken to coat. Refirgerate 2 to 4 hours. Heat 2 tablespoons oil over high heat. Add ginger. Cook 15 seconds, stirring constantly. Add pepper. Stir fry 2 minutes. Add onion. Stir fry 1 minute. Tranfer to bowl. Add rest of oil. Add chicken and red pepper. Stir fry 2 minutes until chicken looses pink color and turns white. Add peanuts, cooked vegetables and soy sauce mixture (soy sauce, water, and cornstarch). Bring to rolling boil, stirring constantly until thick. Serve immediately, discard ginger. Serve with rice.'),(42,'Scallops','https://www.onceuponachef.com/images/2022/03/how-to-cook-scallops-2-scaled.jpg','salt - pepper - rice vinegar - soy sauce - garlic - sugar - green onions','Brown w/ salt and pepper. Serve over glass noodles, top with chopped green onions and toasted sesame seeds.'),(43,'Cheese Fondue','https://images.getrecipekit.com/20220114151652-fondue-20pot-20with-20melted-20fondue-20-2.png?aspect_ratio=1:1&quality=90&','mexican blend cheese - salsa - chopped artichoke hearts - spinach - cumin - tortilla chips','Melt cheese and combine with rest of ingredients. Bake with cumin on top and serve warm with tortilla chips.'),(44,'Golden Nugget Beef','https://www.goldennugget.com/globalassets/las-vegas/restaurants/vics-pork-chop-995x525.jpg','oranges - sugar - cornstarch - soy sauce - ginger - pepper - unsalted beef boullion - water - flank steak - vegetable oil - onion - minced garlic - celery','Peel oranges, remove outer membrance. Cut into 4 slices per orange, cut slices in half. Place in bowl, mix sugar and soy sauce. Pour over oranges. Let stand 15 minutes. Stir occasionally. Set aside. Combine cornstarch, ginger and pepper. Blend in boullion and water. Stir until smooth. Set aside. Cut flank diagonally into very thin slices. Heat 1 tbsp of oil in large skillet on high heat. Cook half of the meat at a 